race.comment: RUBILACE (5) missed a nose at her only start at the track and presents third up this time around in a suitable assignment. Got too far back at Kembla Grange last time but went close at Moruya first-up. Is back after 9 days and Jess Taylor stays aboard. CAPITAL BABE (12) did a good job at Canberra first-up and then was slow off there last time and was caught wide after. Finally draws a low gate and Martin is reunited. Kept on the fresh side and can go better. JUNGLE LIGHTS (10) debuts and brings two trial placings from Kembla Grange. Draws to advantage and the blinkers are on suggesting intent. SABLONNEUSE (3) has a wide gate but is worth a look first up.
